answers.body_markdown:
The argument passed to the click function is incorrect. The click() method triggers the click event, or attaches a function to run when a click event occurs.

**SYNTAX**

Trigger the click event for the selected elements:
```
$(selector).click()
```
Attach a function to the click event:
```
$(selector).click(function)
```
You can as well use the **on() method**. The on() method attaches one or more event handlers for the selected elements and child elements.

Therefore, you can do this
```
$(document).ready(function () {

      $(&quot;#Searchbut&quot;).on(&#39;click&#39;, function () {

          $.ajax({
              url: &quot;https://api.openweathermap.org/data/2.5/weather?q=Chennai&amp;APPID=09e7a4e8ee418a607b4fcec06929900e&quot;,
              async: true,
              type: &quot;GET&quot;,
              dataType: &quot;json&quot;,
              success: function (data) {
                  $(&quot;#weather&quot;).text(Math.floor(data.main.temp - 273.15) + decodeURI(&#39;%C2%B0&#39;) + &quot;C&quot;)///Add the weather from api
                  $(&quot;#location&quot;).text(data.name);
                  $(&#39;#Status&#39;).text(data.weather[0].main)
                  if (data.weather[0].icon == &quot;10n&quot;) {
                      var imgurl = &quot;/Images/showerrain.jpg&quot;
                      $(&#39;#Weather-Header&#39;).css(&#39;background-image&#39;, &#39;url(https://media.giphy.com/media/t7Qb8655Z1VfBGr5XB/giphy.gif)&#39;, &#39;background-size&#39;, &#39;cover&#39;, &#39;background-repeat&#39;, &#39;no-repeat&#39;);
                  }
                  alert(data);
              },
              error: function (ex) {

                  console.log(&quot;Error&quot;);
              }

          });
      });
```
